finalproject.utilities

Class Shooter

  • java.lang.Object
    • finalproject.utilities.Shooter

  • public class Shooter
extends java.lang.Object
    Shooter class uses odometry to turn robot to selected target. Then shoots a ball at the target. Currently uses a fixed angle but later on if 1.RObot position is known and 2. Target position is known, the angle to turn to could be calculated. Tuesday February 14, 2017 9:45am
    Author:
    thomaschristinck, alexmasciotra

    • Constructor Detail

      • Shooter

        public Shooter(lejos.hardware.motor.EV3LargeRegulatedMotor shooterMotorL,
       lejos.hardware.motor.EV3LargeRegulatedMotor shooterMotorR)
        This is the initializer. It gets the wheel motors from the odometer. The shooter motors should be passed when the initializer is called. The arm should be raised and the scoop should be clear of objects.

      • Shooter

        public Shooter(lejos.hardware.motor.EV3LargeRegulatedMotor shooterMotorL,
       lejos.hardware.motor.EV3LargeRegulatedMotor shooterMotorR,
       boolean armRaised)
        Constructor for Shooter class.
        Parameters:
        shooterMotorL - Left shooter motor object.
        shooterMotorR - Right shooter motor object.
        armRaised - True if the launch arms are raised, i.e. 90 degrees to the horizon.

    • Method Detail

      • shoot

        public void shoot()
        This can be called when the robot is in a position to shoot.

      • raiseArm

        public void raiseArm()
        Slowly raises the launch arm to the vertical position to reduce robot size. Sets armRaised flag.

      • lowerArm

        public void lowerArm()
        Slowly raises the launch to an angle above the horizon to the robot to move with the ball. Removes armRaised flag.

      • collect

        public void collect()
        Lowers the arm to collect the ball. Sets hasBall flag to true.

      • raiseArmWithBall

        public void raiseArmWithBall()
        Raises the arm to move with the ball. Only call after lowerArmToCollect has been called. This method roughly raises the launch arm parallel to the horizon.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops both motors.

      • floatMotor

        public void floatMotor()
        Floats both launch motors.

      • setAdjustMode

        public void setAdjustMode()
        Set acceleration and speed to smoothly move the launch arm up and down.

      • setShootMode

        public void setShootMode()
        Set acceleration and speed to shooting mode.

      • rotateTo

        public void rotateTo(int angle)
        Rotate arm to an angle.
